the group.\n+  - If the bot does not receive group messages, disable privacy via @BotFather: /setprivacy \u2192 select your bot \u2192 Disable.\n \n-if __name__ == '__main__':\n-    asyncio.run(get_chat_id())\n-```\n+### Find your chat ID\n \n-</details>\n+You can get your `chat_id` by sending a message to the [GetIDs bot](https://t.me/getidsbot).\n \n-<ComponentConfiguration meta={ComponentMetadata} config={config} />\n+### Configure Viseron\n+\n+- Put the numeric ID(s) in `telegram_chat_ids`.\n+- You can list multiple IDs to notify several chats.\n+\n+For more thorough instructions, see the Home Assistant Telegram docs:\n+https://www.home-assistant.io/integrations/telegram/\n+\n+## Available commands\n+\n+To find the available commands you can use, send `/help` to your bot in Telegram.\n \n ## Troubleshooting\n \ndiff --git a/viseron/components/ptz/__init__.py b/viseron/components/ptz/__init__.py\nindex 18e937f4e..ace8ec7b9 100644\n--- a/viseron/components/ptz/__init__.py\n+++ b/viseron/components/ptz/__init__.py\n@@ -183,14 +183,6 @@ def _camera_registered(self, event: Event[AbstractCamera]) -> None:\n                             camera.identifier, preset[CONFIG_PRESET_NAME]\n                         )\n \n-    def get_registered_cameras(self) -> dict[str, AbstractCamera]:\n-        \"\"\"Get the registered cameras.\"\"\"\n-        return self._cameras\n-\n-    def get_camera(self, camera_identifier: str) -> AbstractCamera | None:\n-        \"\"\"Get a camera by identifier.\"\"\"\n-        return self._cameras.get(camera_identifier)\n-\n     async def patrol(\n         self,\n         camera_identifier: str,\ndiff --git a/viseron/components/telegram/__init__.py b/viseron/components/telegram/__init__.py\nindex d19815209..f3067e079 100644\n--- a/viseron/components/telegram/__init__.py\n+++ b/viseron/components/telegram/__init__.py\n@@ -1,19 +1,16 @@\n-\"\"\"PTZ over Telegram.\"\"\"\n+\"\"\"Telegram component.\"\"\"\n \n from __future__ import annotations\n \n impor